{
  "doc_id": "60407",
  "text": "The description of Geophis turbidus Pavón-Vázquez, Canseco-Márquez & Nieto-Montes de Oca, 2013, contains information on morphological variation, distribution, natural history, and conservation [CITATION_1] . In this study, we report the occurrence of G. turbidus in Hidalgo state, Mexico, for the first time, and we also include information on the species' natural history, as well as the morphological description of a juvenile (scutellation and color pattern), which is not available in the original description [CITATION_2] . Based on the little information that exists on the species, our new data adds to the knowledge on morphological variation, potential distribution in different environments, and how best to conserve this recently described species. ",
